translated: Een, Katarina (Karin) Eugenia, rector, Skara, born October 4, 1886 in Visby to the mayor Carl Julius Teodor E. and Maria Teresia Goijer. She passed her high school teacher exam in Stockholm in 1908, received a diploma in geography in 1922, and in French in 1928 from the fourth division there. She also obtained exams and diplomas from the Institute d'Études Francaises de Tourraine in 1928 and participated in holiday courses organized by school principalship in French in Djursholm in 1917 and in Strängnäs in 1922. She traveled to Germany and Belgium for geographical studies in 1910, to French and Bavarian Alps, Saxon Switzerland in 1921, Harz in 1922, Holland and France in 1931, Italy in 1939, to Paris and Bouliogne sur Mer for language studies in 1910, Grenoble in 1921, and to Paris and Tours in 1928. She worked at Eksjö Hick-lärov from 1910-1913, Visby högre flickskola from 1913-1919, Margaretaskolan in Stockholm from 1919-1920, Lychous-ka skolan from 1920-1921, Stockholm högre folkskola from 1921-1922, Härnöisands elementary school and more from 1922-1925, folk and småskoleseminarium and högre flickskola at Ateneum in Stockholm from 1926-1930, Oscarsskolan from 1928-1930, Stockholm lärl:skola at the same time, Skara högre flickskola from 1930-1935, subject teacher, and rector of Skara municipal girls' school since 1935. She was the vice chairman of the dental clinic, secretary of the Skarab. 1. scout-promotion, treasurer of the association Nordens Skaraavd., and a member of the church council, Skara school children's paint club, and RPO local branch. She was also a member of the board for Skara school home, Skara school vacation colonies, and the board of the people's school. She married but no year was mentioned.
